                        <h2 id="1" class="h4" >What kind of information do we collect?</h2>
                            <p>
                                Most of the information that we collect about you comes directly from you when 
                                you use our App, or interact with advertising or other Services. Broadly the 
                                information we collect about you relates to the type of device you are using, 
                                how you use our App (such as levels attempted and purchases made) and may include
                                information that you submit when creating an account with us or which you allow
                                us to access when you connect to your social network accounts through our App. 
                                We may also collect information from advertising platforms, partners and other 
                                third parties such as information about purchases and interests.<br>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                In more detail, depending on which of our Services you interact with we may collect and process the following types of information:
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Information you provide: information you directly give us, such as name, email, password, 
                                    voice recording provided via the App, or any content you share on MiniForum.</li>
                        
                                    <li>If you choose not to create an account by connecting your social media account, 
                                    the information that we collect when you use our App will be anonymous, but we will collect device 
                                    level identifiers and other information associated with those identifiers including:</li>
                            
                                    <li>the type of device(s) you are using to use our App or access our Services, identifiers such as 
                                    IP address, device identifiers, ad identifiers, a specific user ID, and the country or region that you 
                                    are using in; and</li>
                            
                                    <li>how you use our App and interact with our Services (such as your progress through the App, session time 
                                    and duration, number of attempts at each level and purchases made).</li>
                            
                                    <li>Device information: we collect information from and about the device you use that integrate with our App. 
                                    Information we obtain from your device include: brand, model, operating system, unique identifiers such as 
                                    device id, and advertising id and other identifier, language, time zone, and connection speed.</li>
                            
                                    <li>Information we collect about you from our other third party companies who have obtained your consent or have 
                                    another legal right to share such information with us (including publishing partners, platforms, 
                                    advertising platforms and partners and data aggregators who have obtained). This may include attributes 
                                    about you and your interests, as well as other services you use, demographic and general location 
                                    information. We will use this information as described in this Privacy Policy and subject to any limitations 
                                    in the privacy policy of the company that collected the information from you.</li>
                            
                                    <li>if you contact us, for instance through our customer service channels, or respond to messages and communications 
                                    that we send to you, we may keep a record of that correspondence;</li>
                                </ul>
                            </p>
                        <h2 id="2" 
                        class="h4">Information obtained by third parties</h2>
                            <p>
                                <b>Social Networks</b>: Where we make this available, you can choose to log in to your SpreSkill Profile 
                                using your account details with a third party network, such as Facebook or Google. Exactly what information 
                                we receive will depend on your settings in your Google/ Facebook account, but typically we will receive your 
                                basic public profile information such as your username, email address, age range, profile picture, gender, 
                                chosen language, country and any other public information. Logging in with Facebook will not allow us to post 
                                anything to your page without your permission. We would recommend that you read Google’s Privacy Policy and 
                                Facebook’s Privacy Policy
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <b>Other third parties</b>: to support, maintain and optimize our Service, we work with a variety of 
                                third-party advertising networks, website analysis firms, such as Google, Facebook, (collectively, “Third Party providers”). 
                                These Third Party Providers collect and use non-personally identifiable information, such as your mobile device ID, 
                                about your use of our App in order to sever you with advertisements tailored to meet your preferences and likely 
                                interests or better understand ad effectiveness. Aggregate Data will also be used for optimizing our user experience 
                                and market research purposes.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                You can opt-out of receiving personalized ads from advertisers and ad networks that are members of the Networks 
                                Advertising Initiative (“NAI”) or who follow the DAA self-Regulatory Principles for Online Behavioral Advertising 
                                using their tool can be found here <a href="http://www.networkadvertising.org/choices/"> http://www.networkadvertising.org/choices/</a> 
                                and the DAA’s opting out tool can be 
                                found here <a href="http://www.aboutads.info/choices/">http://www.aboutads.info/choices/</a>
